      <strong>When first playing Mei it might be very confusing what determines where the wall will be placed.</strong> Of course you have the little indicator, but in the heat of the battle there is no time to go looking for this. In reality it's actually fairly simple. Think of the world as a 2 dimensional picture. <strong>Draw a line down from your crosshair, whatever object (or floor) it hits first is where the wall will be placed</strong> (As long as it is within the 35 meter range). Only static object affect the position, meaning you can't place it on anything that can be moved. <br>
      All this will take some getting used to, but once you realise what is going on, you will quickly be placing your walls like a pro.
